This article is a message from President Barack Obama to the Senate regarding a tax treaty with France. The President is transmitting a proposed protocol to amend the Convention between the United States and France for the Avoidance of Double Taxation and the Prevention of Fiscal Evasion with Respect to Taxes on Income and Capital. The proposed protocol aims to eliminate withholding taxes on certain cross-border direct dividend and royalty payments. It also includes provisions for mandatory arbitration in unresolved cases and measures to prevent "treaty shopping" and facilitate the exchange of information between tax authorities. The President recommends that the Senate give early and favorable consideration to the proposed protocol and consent to its ratification. The message was sent on September 9, 2009.